Returns the character matrix or phylogeny from a treedata.table object

pull.treedata.table.Rd

Returns the character matrix or phylogeny from a treedata.table object

pull.treedata.table(tdObject, type = "dat")

Arguments

tdObject

A treedata.table object
type

Whether the output of the function is a tree ('type="phylo"') or a data.table ('type="dat"')

Value

A data.table or phylo object from the original treedata.table object

Examples

data(anolis)
td <- as.treedata.table(anolis$phy, anolis$dat)
#> Phylo object detected 
#> No tips were dropped from the original tree/dataset
pull.treedata.table(td, type = "phy")
#> 
#> Phylogenetic tree with 100 tips and 99 internal nodes.

#> Tip labels:

#> Rooted; includes branch lengths.
pull.treedata.table(td, type = "dat")
